{
  "texts": [
    "With the closed-form expression for the optimal policy under the reward model r ϕ, we can derive the corresponding gradient needed to optimize it by differentiating the negative ML loss with respect to ϕ:",
    "policy answers",
    "See Appendix A.2 for the proof.",
    "Intuitively, the gradient shapes the reward signal by increasing r ϕ (a, q) on expert answers and decreasing it on policy answers, thus nudging the policy toward the expert distribution.",
    "A concrete algorithm for the alternating optimization is given in Algorithm 4 in Appendix E."
  ]
}